<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-31T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-31T08:00:00-05:00" n="874" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/885</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-31T14:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            31, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 1, 1918, 3.26
                                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1251. My 1245 [1224], December 26 [24], 10 a.m. Finnish government
                                sending representatives to all European governments to request
                                recognition of independence. Delegation to Washington will be
                                composed of Dr. <persName corresp="#p_IKB1">Ignatius</persName> and
                                Professor <persName corresp="#p_RJN1">Julio Reuter</persName>;
                                latter now here and member of a delegation to Danish, Norwegian
                                Governments after which will proceed United States via England.
                                British Minister informs me he has been instructed to tell
                                delegation they could proceed to London and would receive
                                sympathetic reception.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_MIN1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>